# ── M1608: converted to full open-source (2026-07-06) — core implementation
# (server.py, static/northstar.html, static/hooks/*.py, scripts/) is now tracked
# and pushed to GitHub alongside PyPI, per the "hub=product, monetize via data
# not code" decision. entity/ and corpus/corpora/ (data-pipeline working dirs,
# not source) stay excluded.
entity/
corpus/
corpora/

# ── M1608-c: REVERTED the /hooks/ exclusion from M1608-b (2026-07-06). It was
# wrong: ~/.claude/settings.json hardcodes hook commands as
# "python3 $HOME/.hub/hooks/northstar-*.py" — the top-level hooks/ symlinks are
# NOT redundant duplication, they're the actual path Claude Code's hook runner
# invokes. Excluding them from git would mean a fresh `git clone` + pip install
# ships a settings.json that points at a directory that doesn't exist until
# someone manually recreates the symlinks — breaking every hook silently.
# static/hooks/*.py (canonical real files) stay tracked either way.

# Demo/test/scratch HTML pages and personal marketing card mockups — no
# adoption value to a first-time visitor, just noise in the public tree.
static/*-test.html
static/*-test2.html
static/gc-test.html
static/waterfall-test.html
static/ns-table-test.html
static/m1355-test.html
static/ns-test2.html
static/landing.html
static/market-signals.html
static/linkedin-card*.html
static/ns-hub-linkedin-card*.html
static/ns-hub-card.html
static/detail-card-v1.html
static/model-char.html
static/characters/

# Dead code — kept locally for reference, never wired into anything live.
hooks/_deprecated/
static/hooks/_deprecated/

# M1608-e: explicitly-disabled hooks (orphaned, not wired into settings.json/server.py)
# kept locally for reference but excluded from the public push — not deploy targets.
hooks/.disabled/
static/hooks/.disabled/

